                "name": "Tejash Raj",
                "href": "/profile/Tejash-Raj-4"
            },
            "answer_text": "Lattice energy or Lattice enthalpy is inversely proportional to size of both cations and anions. Let's take NaF and NaCl as examples :- NaF has fluoride ion which have size smaller than size of chloride ion in NaCl. So, NaF have greater lattice energy than NaCl. Similarly, In case of NaBr and KBr :- Size of sodium ion is smaller as compared to potassium ion so, NaBr has greater lattice energy than KBr. Thank You ! ",
